OL,6,FSenior coroner Catherine Mason had
OL,7,Ftold the jury they should "accept and
OL,8,Ffollow" the findings of the Air
OL,9,FAccidents Investigation Branch (AAIB)
OL,10,Finvestigation into the crash,
OL,11,Fincluding that the pilot's actions
OL,12,Fwere "appropriate and did not
OL,13,Fcontribute to the loss of control".
OL,15,F"An inquest is not a criminal trial,
OL,16,Fit is not a process for apportioning
OL,17,Fblame. It is important to remember
OL,18,Fthat the inquest is simply an attempt
OL,19,Fto establish the facts."
