OL,6,FThe inquest had been told by Mark
OL,7,FJarvis, a principal inspector for the
OL,8,FAAIB, that the helicopter spun because
OL,9,Fof a mechanical fault of a bearing in
OL,10,Fthe tail rotor which became "seized"
OL,11,Fafter its lubrication broke down
OL,12,Fcausing a control shaft to rotate and
OL,13,Fbecome unscrewed.
